**My Dearest Eleanor,  


I write this with a trembling hand and a heart heavy with the weight of years unspoken and the weight of storms unweathered.  

The sea, it has risen against the horizon, it has risen against the sky, it has risen against the soul.  

I have been a solitary sentinel in this solitary station for five solitary seasons.  

But tonight, it is not a night for nights for nightlings;  

It is a night of hows and hows and hows and hows and hows;  

I have been a wraith in this wraith of wraiths and the wraith of wraiths and the wraith of wraiths;  

